        "content": "<p>Hi everyone.</p>\n<p>While reading Chapter 7 of Mathematics in Lean, there are several ways to associate to an operation a symbol.</p>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">One‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"sd\">/-- The element one -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">one</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">inherit_doc</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"ùüô\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">One‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">one</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Dia‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">dia</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">infixl</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">70</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ‚ãÑ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Dia‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dia</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Inv‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"sd\">/-- The inversion function -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">inv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">inherit_doc</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">postfix</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">max</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"‚Åª¬π\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Inv‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inv</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LE‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"sd\">/-- The Less-or-Equal relation. -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">inherit_doc</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">infix</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ‚â§‚ÇÅ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LE‚ÇÅ</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">le</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SMul‚ÇÉ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Œ≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"sd\">/-- Scalar multiplication -/</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">smul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ±</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Œ≤</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">infixr</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">73</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ‚Ä¢ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SMul‚ÇÉ</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">smul</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I guess, the first one is standard for constants, but how do the other ones work?<br>\nWhat is the number next to \"infixl\" or \"infixr\" and what's the difference between these two?<br>\nWhy is it different for the inversion and the less and or equal relation?</p>",
