    {
        "content": "<p>There's more in-depth guidance/documentation for this specific question here: <a href=\"https://lean-lang.org/lean4/doc/notation.html\">https://lean-lang.org/lean4/doc/notation.html</a></p>\n<p><code>infixl</code> and <code>infixr</code> desugar to <code>notation</code>. The numbers are used to control operator precedence. Precedence is how tightly each operator binds to its operands, and is the difference between <code>a + b + c</code> parsing as <code>(a + b) + c</code> and parsing as <code>a + (b + c)</code>.</p>",
